[Claudius] I have nothing with this answer, Hamlet. These
words are not mine.
[Hamlet] No, nor mine. Now, my lord, you played once
i'th' university, you say?
[Polonius] That did I, my lord, and was accounted a good
actor
[Hamlet] And what did you enact?
[Polonius] I did enact Julius Caesar. I was killed i'th' Capitol.
Brutus killed me.
[Hamlet] It was a brute part of him to kill so capital a
