[Osric] I thank your lordship, 'tis very hot.
[Hamlet] No, believe me, 'tis very cold. The wind is
northerly.
[Osric] It is indifferent cold, my lord, indeed.
[Hamlet] Methinks it is very sultry and hot for my
complexion.
[Osric] Exceedingly, my lord, it is very sultry, as 'twere--
I cannot tell how. But, my lord, his majesty bade me
